                          NASA Glenn Projects On-Line

   The Glenn Research Center is the Center of Excellence for aerospace
   technology and development where aeropropulsion and space applications
   form a synergistic relationship that enables the NASA mission and
   improves the quality of life on Earth. NASA Glenn has a long-standing
   reputation for its expertise in project management. Listed below are
   two listings of Glenn projects which have web pages. Historical
   projects may listed on the Glenn History page.

Interagency Projects

   The web sites listed below are for projects in which the Glenn Research
   Center leads or participates in and it does not represent a
   comprehensive listing of projects at Glenn.

     Advanced Communication Technology Satellite (ACTS)
     Aero Propulsion Systems Base R&T Program
     Aviation Safety Program
     Breakthrough Propulsion Physics Program
     Cassini
     Chemical Equilibrium with Applications Program (CEA)
     Combined Cycle Propulsion
     Deep Space 1
     Earth Observing-1 (EO-1)
     Environmental Research Aircraft and Sensor Technology (ERAST)
     General Aviation Propulsion (GAP) Program
     High Performance Computing and Communications (HPCC) Project
     Higher Operating Temperature Propulsion Components (HOTPC) Project
     Integrated Financial Management Program (IFMP)
     International Space Station

     Electrical Power System
     Fluids & Combustion Facility (FCF)

     Mars Airplane

     Microgravity Science Missions

     Nanotechnology Project

     Nuclear Thermal Rocket (NTR) [currently unavailable]

     Oil-Free Turbomachinery Program

     Outsourcing Desktop Initiative for NASA (ODIN)

     Pulse Detonation Engine (PDE) Technology

     Revolutionary Aeropropulsion Concepts

     Scientific and Technical Information (STI) Program

